What is a reservable object:
 - An object which can be reserved.
 - A reservable object can be set as non-reservable. (For-instance due to maintenance).
 - Has a location.
 - Has a list of known complications.

What is a reservation:
 - A reservation is a 'time-claim' anyone can put on a reservable object.
 - A reservation has a start-time and an end-time which is after the start-time.
    + The start-time may be in the past, only an admin can create a reservation that ends in the past.
    + The start-time and end-time may be on different dates, as long as start < end.
 - A reservation has a reference to a person (or group?).
 - A reservation has a function which can calculate any costs related to that reservation.
 - A reservation has a log, which the user must fill in after the reservation has ended.

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

What is a boat:
 - A boat is part of our or any external fleet of boats.
 - A boat can be any type of boat.
 - A boat requires a certain skipper-ship.
 - A boat can have a limited amount of persons on board.
 - A boat can have an engine.


What is a boat reservation:
 - A boat reservation can be linked to a training (or event),
   if it is not it must have an assigned scipper who is allowed to take the boat.
 - If the boat has an engine a user can set an amount of engine-hours used.

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

What is a gear-piece:
 - A gear-piece is any wearable item used for sailing.
 - Is of a type.
 - Has a size measure.

What is a gear-piece reservation:
 - A gear-piece reservation can be linked to a person or training (or event).

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

What is a room:
 - A room is a place the Loefbijter owns which can be used by any party within the Loefbijter.
   (This does not include the VvS)
 - A room has a limited capacity.
 - A room has a location/address.

What is a room reservation:
    - A reservation made by any user or group with the needed permissions.





 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

As a user I want to be able to make a reservation for an available reservable object

As a user I want to see an hourly availability diagram showing when reservable objects are already claimed.

As a user I want to be able to update the amount of engine-hours I made after my reservation ended so that I can be a fair person.

As a user I want to be able to fill in a logbook so that I can inform the board of any issues/additional usage.





















